Due to the nature of the Cloud Rendering GE the renderer cannot be ran in FIWARE Lab. The renderer needs GPU virtualization that is not available at this point in FIWARE nor in cloud hosting platforms in general. The web service can be ran as instances but they are still under construction. 
Follow these steps to get an instance of the web service of the Cloud Rendering GE:

 Login to http://cloud.lab.fiware.org with your credentials 
 Create a security group under the "Security" section, and open port number 22 (for SSH access if wanted), port number 80, and port number 3000 for both TCP and UDP; 
 Navigate to "Images" and select "clour-rendering-X.X.X", where X.X.X stands for version number (for example 3.3.3). Click on "Launch"; 
 In step 2 of the "Launch Instances" window called "Access & Security", be sure to check your new created security group when creating the instance. 
 Finish creating the instance, no further custom options are required; 
 The instance will appear in the "Instances" section. Please wait until the "Status" column shows "ACTIVE", the "Task" column shows "none", and "Power state" is "RUNNING"; 
 Attach a floating IP address in the "Security" section, so you can access it from anywhere on the internet. 

 You will be able to run the stack by running the web service on the cloud and renderers on dedicated hardware that can handle the 3D rendering aspects it depends on (full OpenGL or DirectX rendering).
